name: Strange Quantum Cube
desc: A small, heavy cube of unknown origin. It hums with a faint, barely perceptible energy.

name: Void Quantum Cube
desc: An ultradense datacore ejected from a Void-class singularity. It hums with phase-incoherent energy and resists all attempts at conventional readout.

name: Hyper Quantum Cube
desc: A crystalline lattice suspended between hyperspace strata. Telemetry shows a persistent micro-delay, as if the cube arrives a heartbeat after it is observed.

name: Pulse Quantum Cube
desc: A resonant core that charges and releases in silent pulses. The waveform matches echoes recorded near Pulse-class dark stars.

name: Strange Decoder (Base)
desc: A modular signal-decoder designed to handshake with Eidolon cubes. Requires a tuned module for a specific field: Hyper, Pulse, or Void.

name: Strange Decoder - Hyper Tuning
desc: Tuned module enabling the Strange Decoder to read phase-drift data from Hyper Quantum Cubes.

name: Strange Decoder - Pulse Tuning
desc: Tuned module enabling the Strange Decoder to capture and phase-lock the pulse envelope emitted by Pulse Quantum Cubes.

name: Strange Decoder - Void Tuning
desc: Tuned module enabling the Strange Decoder to translate the low, nonlocal hum of Void Quantum Cubes.

name: UAF Flight Recorder
desc: Recovered data module from a UAF prototype destroyed near a Black Star. Contains fragmented telemetry and distress bursts recorded seconds before the first 'Echo Fleet' contact; much of it is marred by phase noise and quantum-slip artifacts. Valuable mission evidence; keep secured for analysis.
